The five-storey residential building under construction in Kinoo and which collapsed had no proper foundation and was not approved by the National Construction Authority (NCA). Experts and Engineers who visited the site said that the building crumbled because it stood on a weak foundation. The building developed cracks before sinking in the early hours of Friday.  No one was injured as masons who were at the site moved to safety on time. Plans are underway to demolish the building with tenants who live close advised to stay away until further notice The incident comes just THREE days after another building collapsed in Kihara, Gachie a few kilometres away from Kinoo. Experts have linked the rampant collapse of buildings to greedy developers dodging approvals from authorities. Also Read: Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis